                <p />
                <p>Annex II, fourth paragraph,</p>
                <p>point 6(b), first indent</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>In general, except baker's honey</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Entry 6(b)(i) of the paragraph 12 table in Schedule 1</p>
                <p />
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>‘Subject to’ wording not included because it has no substantive legal value and only text with a legal purpose can be included in the Regulations.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Annex II, fourth paragraph,</p>
                <p>point 6(b), second indent</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Honeys of declared origin from regions with tropical climate and blends of these honeys</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Entry 6(b)(ii) of the paragraph 12 table in Schedule 1</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
      <paragraph>
        <content>
          <p>Additional requirements of Directive 2014/63/EU (amending the Honey Directive), i.e. insofar as its provisions do not relate to direct amendments made to the Honey Directive:</p>
          <table uk:widths="2.96in 1.43in 4.54in 5.61in">
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Article in Directive 2014/63/EU</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Objective</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Provision in the Honey (England) Regulations 2015</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Comments</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Article 1</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Amends the Honey Directive</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>See the previous table</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Article 2(1), first sub-paragraph, first sentence</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Obligation to transpose</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>The provisions of the Honey (England) Regulations 2015 implement the Directive provisions.</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Article 2(1), first sub-paragraph, second sentence</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Notification of text to Commission</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Not for the text of the 2015 Regulations</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>DEFRA policy colleagues will notify the Commission of the implementation.</p>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Article 2(1), second sub-paragraph</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Reference to Directive</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>The first paragraph of  the Explanatory Note for the 2015 Regulations contains a statement that the Regulations implement the Honey Directive.</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Article 2(2)</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Application date</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Regulation 1(1) (coming into force date)</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Article 3</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Transitional measures</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Regulation 22</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Article 4</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Entry in force</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Does not need to be transposed into domestic legislation</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>The 2015 Regulations come into force on 24h June 2015, which is the implementation date for  Directive 2014/63/EU.</p>
                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Article 5</p>
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Addressed to Member States</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
                <p>Does not need to be transposed into domestic legislation</p>
                <p />
              </td>
              <td>
                <p />
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table>
        </content>
      </paragraph>
    </mainBody>
  </doc>
